<bibRefCitation author="FAO" box="[382,515,1398,1422]" pageId="30" pageNumber="2242" refId="ref23310" refString="Four species are likely to be found in the Gulf of Guinea (Shipp, 1981) and two were recorded by Irvine from Ghana. On average about 75 tonnes of triggerfishes are reported to be caught in the region each year (FAO, 2000)." type="book" year="2000">FAO, 2000</bibRefCitation>
), making it an important fishery species.
</paragraph>
